The paper presents a framework for approximate inference algorithms that take advantage of structured representations, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses bias-variance trade-offs, which is a common topic in data science (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for scalable and accurate inference, which is a common topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
